6 An Act relating to state government; defining term;
prohibiting use of state funds or resources for
7 designated purposes; prohibiting display of certain
flags on state property; providing for codification;
8 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
9
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13001 of Title 74, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. As used in this section, "agency" means any agency, board,
17 commission, department, or other state government entity created
18 pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma Constitution or the
19 Oklahoma Statutes.
20 B. No funds or resources may be used by any agency to develop,
21 organize, administer, engage in, promote, or endorse any activity,
22 including any event, initiative, official communication, social
23 media post, educational program, or public campaign, that aims to
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1219 Page 1

1 prom ote or recognize Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, Queer, and
2 Intersex Pride Month or any event with a similar theme.
3 C. No flag that represents sexual orientation or gender
4 identity may be displayed by an agency on state property or grounds.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
6 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
